bugs

Class Parser

  • java.lang.Object
    • bugs.Parser

  • public class Parser
extends java.lang.Object
    Parser for numeric expressions. Used as starter code for the Bugs language parser in CIT594, Spring 2015.
    Version:
    February 2015
    Author:
    Dave Matuszek

        <expression> ::= <arithmetic expression> {  <comparator> <arithmetic expression> }
        A SyntaxException will be thrown if the add_operator is present but not followed by a valid <expression>.
        Returns:
        true if an expression is parsed.

      • isAllbugsCode

        public boolean isAllbugsCode()
        Tries to build an <allbugs code> on the global stack. 
        <allbugs code> ::= "Allbugs" "{" <eol>
                       { <var declaration> }
                       { <function definition> }
                  "}" <eol>
        A SyntaxException will be thrown if the 'Allbugs' is not followed by a "{", or if there is no eol after the first "{", or if the final "}" is not present, or if there is an error with the final eol of the allbugs code.
        Returns:
        true if an allbugs code is parsed.

        A SyntaxException will be thrown if the variable is is present but not followed by a "=", or if the "=" is not followed by a valid <expression>, or if the <expression> is not followed by a valid <eol>.
        Returns:
        true if an assignment statement is parsed.

        public boolean isBlock()
        Tries to build a <block> on the global stack. 
        <block> ::= "{" <eol> { <command> } "}" <eol>

        Returns:
        true if a block is parsed.

      • isBugDefinition

        public boolean isBugDefinition()
        Tries to build a <bug definition> on the global stack. 
        <bug definition> ::= "Bug" <NAME> "{" <eol>
                       { <var declaration> }
                       [ <initialization block> ]
                       <command>
                       { <command> }
                       { <function definition> }
                  "}" <eol>
        A SyntaxException will be thrown if the 'Bug' is not followed by a valid name, or if the first "{" is not present, or if there is no eol after the first "{", or if the necessary command does not appear where it should, or if the final "}" is not present, or if there is an error with the final eol of the definition.
        Returns:
        true if a Bug definition is parsed.

      • nextToken

        Token nextToken()
        Returns the next Token. Increments the global variable lineNumber when an EOL is returned.
        Returns:
        The next Token.

      • pushBack

        void pushBack()
        Returns the most recent Token to the tokenizer. Decrements the global variable lineNumber if an EOL is pushed back.

      • makeTree

        void makeTree(int rootIndex,
              int... childIndices)
        Assembles some number of elements from the top of the global stack into a new Tree, and replaces those elements with the new Tree.

        Caution: The arguments must be consecutive integers 1..N, in any order, but with no gaps; for example, makeTree(2,4,1,5) would cause problems (3 was omitted).

        Parameters:
        rootIndex - Which stack element (counting from 1) to use as the root of the new Tree.
        childIndices - Which stack elements to use as the children of the root.
